# Engineering

## Structure

- HTTP handlers orchestrate; domain rules live in services; aggregations in read-models or projections — not duplicated in the UI or route handlers.
- Do not break API contracts unless explicitly requested.

## When you touch…

- **API endpoints:** keep validation, auth guards, OpenAPI/Swagger, and tests aligned — see [docs/internal/agent-spec.md](../../docs/internal/agent-spec.md).
- **Database:** migration required; follow existing soft-delete and indexing patterns.
- **Infrastructure:** follow [docs/infra/README.md](../../infra/README.md); consider blast radius for production-affecting changes.

## Quality

- Run relevant checks before finishing (`make check` or targeted tests). If tests were skipped, state why explicitly.
- Ledger- or migration-affecting work: integration tests per [docs/testing.md](../../docs/testing.md).

## Stack reference

Next.js (App Router) frontend, Fastify API, PostgreSQL. Details in [docs/architecture.md](../../docs/architecture.md).
